She got me wasted
The way she’s making me lie
Hung from her bracelet
Her lucky charm if I like

The way I’m chasing the night
I don’t wanna go home
Am I losing control

She’s so bitter
She’s so sweet
Lemonade
Lemonade
A little taste
Is all I need
Lemonade
Lemonade
 
She got me waking
At times that I’ve never seen
Bright yellow spaceship
Might make me start to believe
Symptoms are stuck on repeat
No point in trying to leave
She got me waking
It’s doing something to me
I don’t wanna go home
 
She’s so bitter
She’s so sweet
Lemonade
Lemonade
A little taste
Is all I need
Lemonade
Lemonade
 
Is it only human
To escape into delusion
And if I should try to prove it
Would I win or would I lose it

#LouisTomlinson #Lemonade #HowDidIGetHere

snippet.title: The Mandalorian Isn't Going To Save Star Wars
snippet.description: The first trailer for The Mandalorian And Grogu movie came out a few days ago, and nobody cared. Which is a bit of a problem when its the first theatrical Star Wars release in six years, and desperately needs to succeed if its to resurrect the franchise. Can Jon Favreau's movie hope to succeed? Will Pedro Pascal have ANOTHER flop to add to his resume? Does anyone even care?

snippet.title: Roza Zərgərli - Одинокая (Премьера клипа)
snippet.description:
Слушать трек на всех цифровых площадках:
https://bnd.lc/odinokayarz

Текст:

Ты в суматохе дней- одинокая
Высказать ему, хочешь многое
От его глаз все по-прежнему ёкает,
Но от любви, вы такие далекие

На журнальный стол
Полетит посуда вдребезги 
Он тот еще актер
Сколько ссор на фоне ревности
Вспоминаешь все,
Сколько парил он тебе мозги,
Но когда напишет, ты опять его простишь
И так отчаянно 
Ты веришь в то, что чувства не случайные
Но почему скажи, снова печальна ты?
Не понимаешь, как к нему остыть
Снова молчание
Любовь давно в режиме ожидания
Летит в окно колечко обручальное
И вместе с ним, совместные мечты

И в печали, и в радости, навсегда
Но слову "навсегда" увы, грош цена
И клятвы вечной верности,
И в богатстве, в бедности,
Чтоб с тобой быть рядом
Не хватило ему смелости

Ты веришь в то, что чувства не случайные

И вместе с ним, совместные мечты

snippet.title: ICH HABE ALLE JURASSIC-DINOS in 100 TAGEN in Minecraft Hardcore GEFANGEN 🦖
snippet.description:
ICH HABE ALLE JURASSIC-DINOS in 100 TAGEN in Minecraft Hardcore GEFANGEN

Yo, was geht ab – hier ist Caster! 
Heute habe ich 100 Tage in einer Jurassic-Welt überlebt, die von unglaublich gefährlichen Dinosauriern wimmelt 😱🦖 Mein Ziel? 👉 Jeden einzelnen von ihnen zu fangen! Von den kleinen Pflanzenfressern 🌱 wie Triceratops, Brachiosaurus und Microraptor bis hin zu den tödlichsten Raubtieren: dem legendären Tyrannosaurus Rex 🦖, dem mutierten Indominus Rex 👹 und dem furchterregenden Distortus, der dich in Sekunden verschlingt 💀. Und das Beste? Ich habe meinen eigenen prähistorischen Zoo gebaut 🏰🦕. Aber das Verrückteste kommt zum Schluss: Ich erschaffe mein eigenes genetisches Monster aus ALLEN Dinosauriern 😳🧬🔥

💥 Schau dir mein LETZTES 100-TAGE-ABENTEUER in HARDCORE an: https://youtu.be/cLe7HLaRf0I?si=_wtmG2FnAfQrJm01
📺 Sieh dir die VORHERIGE FOLGE an: https://youtu.be/ZMmNbxh4DxM?si=FpR4p-q_F8YFWGKo
🔥 Und hier die ALLERERSTE FOLGE: https://youtu.be/a7NXiYRNA-4?si=V1PoCHWddMoiYrJm

snippet.title: Cher - If I Could Turn Back Time (Cher - The Farewell Tour, 11/08/2002)
snippet.description:
Cher singing 'If I Could Turn Back Time' on 'The Farewell Tour' in Miami on November 8, 2002.

Cher releases Live Album 'The Farewell Tour' for the first time on digital & vinyl September 26, 2025.

Available on Limited-Edition Hot Pink & Purple Vinyl.

ORDER/LISTEN HERE: https://cher.lnk.to/TheFarewellTour

August 8, 2025 (Los Angeles, CA) – Celebrating one of the most memorable tours in history, Cher will release her classic concert album, The Farewell Tour, on 2LP Vinyl and streaming platforms for the first time ever on September 26, 2025 via Warner Records. The exclusive physical edition will be pressed on hot pink and purple 2LP vinyl.

Order the 2LP Vinyl: https://store.warnermusic.com/en/warner-music-store/warner-records/cher/?srsltid=AfmBOoqSOruN8yzdbFrfYKD2__UykUEuWfN4u5IBxO5Jl5WDj0jgvi8X
.
Listen to The Farewell Tour on all DSPs: https://cher.lnk.to/TheFarewellTour

The newly remastered and timeless collection features three tracks, “Save Up All Your Tears,” “We All Sleep Alone” and “Different Kind of Love Song,” which were previously only included on the EMMY® Award-winning special and multiplatinum concert film Live! The Farewell Tour. 
During 2002, the Academy® Award-winning and GRAMMY® Award-winning Rock and Roll Hall of Fame® Inductee and Kennedy Center® Honoree embarked on Living Proof: The Farewell Tour, circling the globe for a staggering 325 shows. The show made history as Cher achieved the Guinness World Record for the “Highest Grossing Tour by a Female Artist” at the time. She chronicled this breathtaking run with Live! The Farewell Tour and accompanying record of the same name and captured her electrifying and unforgettable performance at American Airlines Arena in Miami, FL on November 7, 2002. The album hit shelves on August 26, 2003, and it was only available on CD… until now…
22 years since its initial release, The Farewell Tour finally makes its first appearance on DSPs and vinyl. It consists of the original 18 songs in addition to boasting three bonus tracks: “Save Up All Your Tears,” “We All Sleep Alone,” and “Different Kind of Love Song.” The set traces a fascinating roadmap through her influential and inimitable catalog highlighted by powerhouse performances of “Believe,” “If I Could Turn Back Time,” “Just Like Jesse James,”and “All Or Nothing,” among others. 

Representing every facet of her creative output from classic albums to music for film, television, and theater, The Farewell Tour also includes a special heartfelt tribute to The Sonny and Cher Show.
Last year, she revealed the career-spanning Forever as a special double vinyl package and one CD configuration. She accompanied it with the digital release of Forever Fan Edition. She was also inducted into the Rock & Roll Hall Of Fame® and capped the year off with her acclaimed autobiography, CHER: The Memoir, Part One, which held the #1 spot on The New York Times Bestseller List.

Order the 2LP Vinyl: https://store.warnermusic.com/en/warner-music-store/warner-records/cher/?srsltid=AfmBOoqSOruN8yzdbFrfYKD2__UykUEuWfN4u5IBxO5Jl5WDj0jgvi8X
.
Listen to The Farewell Tour on all DSPs: https://cher.lnk.to/TheFarewellTour

The newly remastered and timeless collection features three tracks, “Save Up All Your Tears,” “We All Sleep Alone” and “Different Kind of Love Song,” which were previously only included on the EMMY® Award-winning special and multiplatinum concert film Live! The Farewell Tour. 
During 2002, the Academy® Award-winning and GRAMMY® Award-winning Rock and Roll Hall of Fame® Inductee and Kennedy Center® Honoree embarked on Living Proof: The Farewell Tour, circling the globe for a staggering 325 shows. The show made history as Cher achieved the Guinness World Record for the “Highest Grossing Tour by a Female Artist” at the time. She chronicled this breathtaking run with Live! The Farewell Tour and accompanying record of the same name and captured her electrifying and unforgettable performance at American Airlines Arena in Miami, FL on November 7, 2002. The album hit shelves on August 26, 2003, and it was only available on CD… until now…
22 years since its initial release, The Farewell Tour finally makes its first appearance on DSPs and vinyl. It consists of the original 18 songs in addition to boasting three bonus tracks: “Save Up All Your Tears,” “We All Sleep Alone,” and “Different Kind of Love Song.” The set traces a fascinating roadmap through her influential and inimitable catalog highlighted by powerhouse performances of “Believe,” “If I Could Turn Back Time,” “Just Like Jesse James,”and “All Or Nothing,” among others. 

Representing every facet of her creative output from classic albums to music for film, television, and theater, The Farewell Tour also includes a special heartfelt tribute to The Sonny and Cher Show.
Last year, she revealed the career-spanning Forever as a special double vinyl package and one CD configuration. She accompanied it with the digital release of Forever Fan Edition. She was also inducted into the Rock & Roll Hall Of Fame® and capped the year off with her acclaimed autobiography, CHER: The Memoir, Part One, which held the #1 spot on The New York Times Bestseller List.
